    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Members of a class containing 2,100 living species of marine invertebrates having a body comprising a central round disk from which radiate five long, slender, fragile arms used for locomotion; the arms can be broken off but quickly regenerate.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>含兩千一百種現存海生無脊椎動物的綱；身體中央具圓形體盤，五隻細長脆弱的腕足從體盤向外呈輻射狀延伸，用以進行移動；其腕足易斷，但也能快速再生。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
